ctes pululahua sp. nov.: holotype ♂, 6.6 × 3.0 mm, cephalothorax 1.57 mm wide, pereiopods 1–3 frontal, uropod dorsal and ventral; paratype ♀, 3.5 mm wide, cephalothorax 1.80 mm wide, second antenna flagellum (Ecuador, Pichincha Prov., Pululahua volcano, altitude 3000 m, leg. L. Bartolozzi, 14 February 1993, MZUF)." captionText-3="Figure 131. Scleropactes pululahua sp. nov.: holotype ♂, 6.6 × 3.0 mm, cephalothorax 1.57 mm wide, pereiopods 4–6 frontal, pereiopod 4 dactylus frontal and caudal (Ecuador, Pichincha Prov., Pululahua volcano, altitude 3000 m, leg. L. Bartolozzi, 14 February 1993, MZUF)." captionText-4="Figure 132. Scleropactes pululahua sp. nov.: holotype ♂, 6.6 × 3.0 mm, cephalothorax 1.57 mm wide, pereiopod 7 frontal and caudal, second antenna ventral, sesond antenna apical cone enlarged (Ecuador, Pichincha Prov., Pululahua volcano, altitude 3000 m, leg. L. Bartolozzi, 14 February 1993, MZUF)." captionText-5="Figure 133. Scleropactes pululahua sp. nov.: holotype ♂, 6.6 × 3.0 mm, cephalothorax 1.57 mm wide, pleopods 1–4 frontal, pleopod 5 caudal; paratype ♀, 3.5 mm wide, cephalothorax 1.80 mm wide, pleopods 1 and 2 frontal (Ecuador, Pichincha Prov., Pululahua volcano, altitude 3000 m, leg. L. Bartolozzi, 14 February 1993, MZUF)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5430342" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5430344" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5430346" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5430348" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5430350" figureDoi-5="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5430352" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5430342/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5430344/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/5430346/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/5430348/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/5430350/files/figure.png" httpUri-5="https://zenodo.org/record/5430352/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Figs 128–133</figureCi